\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4.7}{\ignorespaces Testing different numbers of replaced patches. {\color  {red} The parameter $c_4$ is used to characterize the number of patches replaced in anomalies, where a larger $c_4$ indicates a greater number of replaced patches. The gaps between the reconstruction errors of the normal data and the anomalies become significantly wider when more patches are replaced, which is consistent with our analysis.}}}{61}{figure.caption.17}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig-synthesized-experiment-results-NRP}{{4.7}{61}{Testing different numbers of replaced patches. {\color {red} The parameter $c_4$ is used to characterize the number of patches replaced in anomalies, where a larger $c_4$ indicates a greater number of replaced patches. The gaps between the reconstruction errors of the normal data and the anomalies become significantly wider when more patches are replaced, which is consistent with our analysis.}}{figure.caption.17}{}}
